properties.headline: Hydrologic Outlook issued January 17 at 10:23AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
A period of heavy snow tonight followed by rain later Saturday will
cause rises on the rivers flowing off the Olympics. Heavy snow will
be followed by rain and could drive the Skokomish River up near
flood stage. The snow level will start near sea level Friday night
and then rise as high as 4000 feet by the end of the storm.
Depending on the rainfall total, increase in snow level, and
potential melting of low elevation snow in the valleys, minor
flooding is possible on the Skokomish as a result.

Please continue to monitor the latest forecast for the next few
days. Details of potential flooding will change as the situation
evolves.

Latest river forecasts available at
water.weather.gov/ahps2/index.php?wfo=sew

NWSheadline: RIVER FLOODING IS POSSIBLE BY SUNDAY FOR THE SKOKOMISH RIVER IN MASON COUNTY
